{"tid":1003980,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"【科技台】SpaceX全尺寸大推力火箭引擎「猛禽」已運抵德州測試場","createTime":"2019-02-01T06:00:35.000Z","updateTime":"2019-02-01T20:32:05.000Z","uid":120678,"like":18,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":15,"replies":[{"pid":"f0a07ee899dec959dc7eb2907c9720f3b8d68711","tid":1003980,"uid":120678,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-02-01T06:00:35.000Z","msg":"外電報導：<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.teslarati.com/spacex-ceo-elon-musk-official-photos-starship-completed-starship-raptor-engine/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.teslarati.com%2Fspacex-ceo-elon-musk-official-photos-starship-completed-starship-raptor-engine%2F&d=WPS43JJkpORccPZf4osG%2FUcTp%2BQsjpNju1TtMRGBB4E%3D&h=ac11a506\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.teslarati.com/spacex-ceo-elon-musk-official-photos-starship-completed-starship-raptor-engine/</a><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/nUfM7Pb.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FnUfM7Pb.jpg&h=b65d08e2&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/4zMDYVR.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2F4zMDYVR.jpg&h=fc78d863&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nEric Ralph<br />\nByEric RalphPosted on January 31, 2019<br />\n<br />\nShortly after Teslarati reported that the first operationalized Raptor had shipped to McGregor, Texas for its first full-scale static fire tests, SpaceX CEO Elon Musk took to Twitter to post the first official photos of the &ldquo;radically redesigned&rdquo; engine preparing for its critical debut test fire in Texas.<br />\n<br />\nDesigned with extreme reliability, efficiency, and reusability in mind, the Raptor seen in Musk&rsquo;s photos is rated for just shy of 2.5 times the thrust of Merlin 1D at 200 tons (450,000 lbf) and has been commonized across both stages of BFR (Starship and Super Heavy) to spread out development costs and speed up the next-generation rocket&rsquo;s orbital launch debut.<br />\n<br />\nAside from revealing some impressive photos of the first upgraded Raptor preparing for a static fire test, Musk went into a bit more detail on the future of the engine and its probable development path, describing Raptor in its current iteration as a sort of compromise between achieving nominal performance and minimizing the cost and timescale to arrive at a flight-ready engine. Currently stationed at SpaceX&rsquo;s McGregor, Texas development and testing facilities, Raptor appears to feature an expansion ratio somewhere in between Merlin 1D (optimized for sea-level) and MVac (optimized for vacuum).<br />\n<br />\nThis increases the stress on the nozzle during ignition and operation at normal atmospheric pressures but it also improves engine efficiency once Starship (or Super Heavy) rises above the thickest parts of Earth&rsquo;s atmosphere, even if a medium-expansion nozzle still can&rsquo;t touch the performance of a giant vacuum-optimized bell like those used by MVac. As such, BFR in its earliest iterations will be significantly less capable than a fully-optimized version of the rocket when it comes to high-energy Earth/lunar orbits and interplanetary trajectories, a challenge that can at least initially be hurdled by accepting much lower nominal payload capabilities and relying on brute-force performance, much like Falcon 9 and Heavy.<br />\n==========================<br />\n200噸推力(最終將升級至250噸)，真空比沖380s，全流量分級燃燒循環，SpaceX火星太空船既動力來源"},{"pid":"6ae96c12395b86ec40e7b0df31168b58393e1dbe","tid":1003980,"uid":18955,"like":45,"dislike":1,"score":44,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2019-02-01T06:08:45.000Z","msg":"呢啲project 真係唔可以比中國人埋堆<br />\n否則真係會超英趕美<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e87aea234470237df26243a81814ad275207f94a","tid":1003980,"uid":79563,"like":2,"dislike":2,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"6ae96c12395b86ec40e7b0df31168b58393e1dbe","tid":1003980,"uid":18955,"like":45,"dislike":1,"score":44,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2019-02-0